# Phase 0 discovery only — a THROWAWAY SmartThings Personal Access Token.
#
# SmartThings PATs created after 30 Dec 2024 expire in 24 hours, so this is
# strictly for one-shot discovery. The durable Path B solution (Phase 2) uses
# the OAuth2 authorization_code flow with refresh-token rotation instead.
#
# Generate a PAT at https://account.smartthings.com/tokens with at least:
#   - List all devices            (r:devices:*)
#   - See all devices             (r:devices:*)
#   - Control all devices         (x:devices:*)
#
# Copy this file to `.env` (which is gitignored) and paste your token below.
SMARTTHINGS_PAT=

# Optional overrides (defaults shown):
# SMARTTHINGS_API_BASE=https://api.smartthings.com/v1
# SOFT_KVM_LOG_LEVEL=info

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Phase 2 — durable OAuth2 auth (replaces the throwaway PAT for normal use)
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Register an OAuth (API-only) app via the SmartThings CLI (see docs/PHASE2_AUTH.md)
# with scopes "r:devices:* x:devices:*" and a PUBLIC HTTPS redirect URI you control
# (SmartThings REJECTS localhost). Then provide the static client credentials.
#
# RECOMMENDED: keep them in 1Password and run via `op run`, e.g.:
#   op run --env-file .env -- uv run soft-kvm work
# with op:// references here (op resolves them into the environment):
# SMARTTHINGS_CLIENT_ID=op://Private/SmartThings soft-kvm/client_id
# SMARTTHINGS_CLIENT_SECRET=op://Private/SmartThings soft-kvm/client_secret
#
# Or, for dev only, plain values:
# SMARTTHINGS_CLIENT_ID=
# SMARTTHINGS_CLIENT_SECRET=
#
# Optional OAuth overrides (defaults shown):
# SMARTTHINGS_REDIRECT_URI=https://mikenoe.com   # MUST be public HTTPS — localhost is rejected
# SMARTTHINGS_SCOPES=r:devices:* x:devices:*
#
# The rotating refresh token is NOT stored here — it lives in the macOS Keychain
# (run `soft-kvm auth init` once to obtain and store it).
